==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Burrel shot
<hw>Bur"rel shot`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Either from annoying the
enemy like a <ets>burrel fly</ets>, or, less probably, fr. F.
<ets>bourreler</ets> to sting, torture.]</ety> <fld>(Gun.)</fld> <def>A
mixture of shot, nails, stones, pieces of old iron, etc., fired from a
cannon at short range, in an emergency.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>burrfish</ent>⟦br⟧
